<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>netcoreapp2.0</TargetFramework>
    <GeneratePackageOnBuild>true</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
    <Authors>Dennis Mitchell</Authors>
    <Company>edennis.com</Company>
    <Description>Provides various classes that assist with .NET Core 2 unit testing.  Among the classes are ObjectExtensions, which provides useful extensions to the Object class (e.g., methods for deep comparison, deep cloning, JSON serialization/deserialization); Json, which provides a fluent API wrapper around Json.NET JToken; Jxml, which provides methods for converting JSON to and from 'JXML' (a special form of XML that includes processing instructions and namespace-specific elements and attributes to aid with the recovery of JSON from XML); and JsonAssert, which provides a highly structured, JSON-file-driven approach to unit testing.</Description>
    <PackageTags>Json Testing JXML XML</PackageTags>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/denmitchell/NetCoreTestingUtilities</PackageProjectUrl>
    <PackageIconUrl>https://github.com/denmitchell/NetCoreTestingUtilities/blob/master/EDennis.NetCoreTestingUtilities/EDennis.NetCoreTestingUtilities/edennis128.png</PackageIconUrl>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/denmitchell/NetCoreTestingUtilities</RepositoryUrl>
    <Version>2.2.0</Version>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>This release contains an attribute called Folder which takes an optional parameter for a path.  The Folder attribute is designed to be used in conjunction with an Xunit Theory attribute.  The Folder attribute returns an IEnumerable of objects representing paths of files in the target folder.  JsonAssert.Execute has been modified to optionally accept a file path as a parameter (as opposed to only accepting a simple file name).  This change makes it easier to use the new Folder attribute with JsonAssert.Execute.</PackageReleaseNotes>
    <AssemblyVersion>2.2.0.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>2.2.0.0</FileVersion>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <Compile Remove="OLDJson2Xml2.cs" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer" Version="2.0.1" />
    <PackageReference Include="JsonDiffPatch" Version="2.0.45" />
    <PackageReference Include="xunit" Version="2.3.1" />
  </ItemGroup>
  
  </Project>
